ilies in the state of Bihar ad the state govt. would make an annual expenditure of Rs. 1800 crore.", "007-normal": "CM has also announced a pension of Rs. 6,000 for journalists above 60 years of age. All those people who have have been in regular service in the area of media person and not getting any pension would be eligible for Bihar Patrakar Samman Yojana (BPSY). Till date, around 2 lakh applicants have applied for the pension under the New Bihar Mukhyamantri Vridhjan Pension Scheme. After verification, a total number of 1,35,928 applicants were found eligible.", "008-normal": "BPSY scheme for media persons is also going to be implemented from 1st April 2019 to ensure that more people opt for becoming journalists."}}